        h1 Tab bar
        p Tab bar is a particular case of Toolbar, but it contains icons (or icons with labels) instead of plain links and inteded to be used with <a href="tabs.html">Tabs</a>.
      h2(data-device-preview="../docs-demos/tabbar-layout.html") Tab bar layout
      p Tab bar layout is almost the same as for Toolbar, but Tab bar has additional <b>"tabbar"</b> class:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;div class="toolbar tabbar"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="toolbar-inner"&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab1" class="tab-link active"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-1"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab2" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-2"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab3" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-3"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab4" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-4"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
      p By default, all Tab bar elements (links) equally spaced along toolbar - they have equal space between each other. But here is important note about links size
      .important-note
        ul
          li
            p On iPhone all links will have the same size equal to [screen width] / [number of links]
          li
            p On iPad all links will be centered with minimal width equal to 105px

      h3(data-device-preview="../docs-demos/tabbar-badges.html") Add badges to icons
      p If you need to add badges to Tab bar icons, just put <code>&lt;span class="badge"&gt;</code> inside of icon:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;div class="toolbar tabbar"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="toolbar-inner"&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab1" class="tab-link active"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-1"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab2" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-2"&gt;
          |                 &lt;span class="badge bg-red"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;
          |             &lt;/i&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab3" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-3"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab4" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-4"&gt;
          |                 &lt;span class="badge bg-green"&gt;15&lt;/span&gt;
          |             &lt;/i&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
      h3(data-device-preview="../docs-demos/tabbar-labels.html") Tab bar with labels
      p If you need to use Tab bar icons with labels we need one more <strong>"tabbar-labels"</strong> class on Tab bar, and to put <code>&lt;span class="tabbar-label"&gt;</code> inside of link:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;div class="toolbar tabbar tabbar-labels"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="toolbar-inner"&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab1" class="tab-link active"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-1"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |             &lt;span class="tabbar-label"&gt;Label 1&lt;/span&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab2" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-2"&gt;
          |                 &lt;span class="badge bg-red"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;
          |             &lt;/i&gt;
          |             &lt;span class="tabbar-label"&gt;Label 2&lt;/span&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab3" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-3"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |             &lt;span class="tabbar-label"&gt;Label 3&lt;/span&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |         &lt;a href="#tab4" class="tab-link"&gt;
          |             &lt;i class="icon demo-icon-4"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          |             &lt;span class="tabbar-label"&gt;Label 4&lt;/span&gt;
          |         &lt;/a&gt;
          |     &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;
      .important-note
        p Note that Tab bar with labels will have more height instead of usual 44px: 50px on iPhone and 55px on iPad
        p Because of more height, you should use "tabbar-labels-fixed" or "tabbar-labels-through" for <a href="navbar-toolbar-layouts.html">Fixed and Through layouts</a> with Tab bar 
      .full-width
        h2.stop-scroll-device Related App Methods
        table.methods-table
          tbody
            tr
              td myApp.hideToolbar(<span>toolbar</span>)
              td Hide specified tab bar.<br><code>toolbar</code> - <span class="parameter-type">HTMLElement</span> or <span class="parameter-type">string</span> (with CSS Selector) of required tab bar. Required.
            tr
              td myApp.showToolbar(<span>toolbar</span>)
              td Show specified tab bar.<br><code>toolbar</code> - <span class="parameter-type">HTMLElement</span> or <span class="parameter-type">string</span> (with CSS Selector) of required tab bar. Required.
      h2 Hide Tabbar Automatically
      p Framework7 allows you to hide/show Tabbar automatically for some Ajax loaded pages where you may not need it. It is useful only when you use through-type layout.
      p To make it work all you need is to add <srong>"no-tabbar"</srong> class to loaded page (<code>&lt;div class="page no-tabbar"&gt;</code>):
      pre
        code
          | &lt;!-- Page has additional "no-tabbar" class --&gt;
          | &lt;div data-page="about" class="page no-tabbar"&gt;
          |   &lt;div class="page-content"&gt;
          |     &lt;div class="content-block"&gt;
          |       &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="#" class="back button"&gt;Go Back&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          |       ...
          |     &lt;/div&gt;
          |   &lt;/div&gt;
          | &lt;/div&gt;

